\par The }{\b\f9 Utility-Record Modifications}{\f9  menu option allows the user to record a sequence of configuration modifications and repeat those changes multiple times.  First, select }{\b\f9 On}{\f9  from the }{\b\f9 Record Modifications}{\f9 
 pop-up menu.  Then, make all desired changes to any configuration view(s).  Next, select }{\b\f9 Off}{\f9  from the }{\b\f9 Record Modificaitons}{\f9  pop-up menu.  Now, all modifications have been recorded.
\par 
\par To repeat the recorded modifications, simply perform a }{\b\f9 Device-Read}{\f9  operation and select }{\b\f9 Play}{\f9  from the }{\b\f9 Record Modifications}{\f9  pop-up menu (alternatively press }{\b\f9 Ctrl+M}{\f9 ).  Be sure to perform a }{\b\f9 
Device-Write}{\f9  operation to effect the change into the device.
\par 
\par To append more modifications to a recording, simply select }{\b\f9 On}{\f9  again.  To delete all recorded modifications, select }{\b\f9 Erase }{\f9 from the }{\b\f9 Record Modifications}{\f9  pop-up menu.  Select }{\b\f9 Off}{\f9 
 upon completion of recording.
\par 
\par A recorded modification list will remain active until erased, or upon a Device-Read or File-Open operation in which a configuration of differing version or type is encountered.  Then, the recording is deleted.  The re
cording is also deleted when the application is exited.
